# Rust source/test files (*.rs) must NEVER be LFS-tracked. In a non-LFS
# checkout an LFS-tracked .rs is a pointer file, which Cargo tries to parse as
# Rust, so `cargo check --all-targets` fails before any test runs.
# `readme_claims.rs` (an active README-claims test suite) and `diagnose_*.rs`
# (two SIMD/GPU divergence diagnostics) were previously LFS-tracked; they are
# now stored as normal text. Guarded by
# crates/scanner/tests/contract/rust_test_sources_are_not_lfs_pointers.rs.
#
# Follow-up (flagged, not yet fixed): the contract *.toml fixtures and the
# proptest-regressions seed below are still LFS-tracked, so a non-LFS checkout
# sees pointers and contracts_runner panics parsing them as TOML. Tracked as an
# audit item; de-LFS scoped to .rs sources for now.
crates/scanner/tests/contracts/*.toml filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
crates/scanner/tests/contracts/companion/*.toml filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
crates/scanner/tests/*.proptest-regressions filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
